'''Comisión Clasificadora de Riesgo''' ('''CCR''') (Risk Rating Commission, RRC) is a [[Chile]]an organization which was established in 1985 with the incorporation of Chilean [[Decree]] Law Nº 3500 for approving or rejecting domestic and foreign debt instruments and equity securities that can be purchased by Pension Funds.  Its risk rating system on equity securities is adopted by some of the [[International Social Security Association]] members.<ref name="chile">{{cite web | title=The relevance of the financial market for optimizing pension fund investment | work= | url=http://www.issa.int/pdf/santiago02/2ferreiro.pdf | accessdate=October 31, 2006 }}</ref>

