{{Infobox company | name = NELO | logo = Nelo logo.svg | logo_size = 250px | caption = | type = | traded_as = | genre = <!-- Only used with media and publishing companies --> | fate = | predecessor = | successor = | foundation = 1978 <!-- {{Start date|df=yes|1978|MM|DD}} --> | founder = Manuel Ramos | location_city = [[Vila do Conde]] | location_country = [[Portugal]] | location = | locations = | area_served = | key_people = | industry = Boat manufacturing | products = Canoes, Kayaks, Boat Equipment | services = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | aum = <!-- Only used with financial services companies --> | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = 80 | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = [http://nelo.eu/en/ Nelo.eu] | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Nelo''' (MAR Kayaks Ltda) is a [[Portugal|Portuguese]] company that designs and manufactures [[kayak]]s and [[canoe]]s for racing, touring, fitness, sea racing, paracanoe, surfski, and slalom. It is currently the most successful brand in the sport, attested by the number of medals won by its boats in the [[London 2012 Olympics]].<ref name="games_report">[http://www.nelo.eu/en/news/article/olympic_games_2012_report/ Nelo Olympic Games Report] Retrieved 3 January 2013</ref>
Nelo was founded in 1978 by Manuel Alberto Ramos (known as Nelo by his friends and family), a former paddler himself and the first Portuguese Canoeing National Champion.<ref name="about_us">[http://www.nelo.eu/en/company/ Nelo About Us page] Retrieved 3 January 2013</ref>
More recently the company has broadened its scope and also provides services and products related to canoeing like organizing race events, training centers, athlete performance analysis, training wear, among others.
==Location== Nelo's headquarters and main factories are based in [[Vila do Conde]], a small city in the north of Portugal.<ref name="about_us" /> Besides the main factory and office, Nelo is spread throughout the world, through its network of official agents and by direct sales.
